\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlcont\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\ri4665\sb100\sa100\f0 Detect Good: At will, the blackguard can detect good as a spell-like ability. This ability duplicates the effects of the spell detect good.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Poison Use: Blackguards are skilled in the use of poison and never risk accidentally poisoning themselves when applying poison to a blade.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Dark Blessing: A blackguard applies his Charisma modifier (if positive) as a bonus to all saving throws.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Spells: Beginning at 1st level, a blackguard gains the ability to cast a small number of divine spells. To cast a spell, the blackguard must have a Wisdom score of at least 10 + the spell\rquote s level, so a blackguard with a Wisdom of 10 or lower cannot cast these spells. Blackguard bonus spells are based on Wisdom, and saving throws against these spells have a DC of 10 + spell level + the blackguard\rquote s Wisdom modifier. When the blackguard gets 0 spells of a given level, such as 0 1st-level spells at 1st level, he gets only bonus spells. (A blackguard without a bonus spell for that level cannot yet cast a spell of that level.) The blackguard\rquote s spell list appears below. A blackguard has access to any spell on the list and can freely choose which to prepare, just like a cleric. A blackguard prepares and casts spells just as a cleric does (though the blackguard cannot spontaneously cast cure or inflict spells).\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Smite Good: Once a day, a blackguard of 2nd level or higher may attempt to smite good with one normal melee attack. He adds his Charisma modifier (if positive) to his attack roll and deals 1 extra point of damage per class level. For example, a 9th-level blackguard armed with a longsword would deal 1d8+9 points of damage, plus any additional bonuses from high Strength or magical effects that normally apply. If the blackguard accidentally smites a creature that is not good, the smite has no effect but it is still used up for that day. Smite good is a supernatural ability.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Aura of Despair: Beginning at 3rd level, the blackguard radiates a malign aura that causes enemies within 10 feet of him to suffer a -2 morale penalty on all saving throws. Aura of despair is a supernatural ability.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Command Undead: When a blackguard reaches 3rd level, he gains the supernatural ability to command and rebuke undead. He commands undead as would a cleric of two levels lower.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Sneak Attack: If a blackguard can catch an opponent when she is unable to defend herself effectively from his attack, he can strike a vital spot for extra damage. Basically, any time the blackguard\rquote s target would be denied her Dexterity bonus to AC (whether she actually has a Dexterity bonus or not) or when the blackguard flanks the target, the blackguard\rquote s attack deals +1d6 points of damage at 4th level and an additional +1d6 points for every three levels thereafter (+2d6 at 7th level, +3d6 at 10th level, and so on). Should the blackguard score a critical hit with a sneak attack, this extra damage is not multiplied.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Ranged attacks only count as sneak attacks if the target is 30 feet away or less. A blackguard cannot make a sneak attack to deal subdual damage. The blackguard must be able to see the target well enough to pick out a vital spot and must be able to reach a vital spot. He cannot sneak attack while striking at a creature with concealment or by striking the limbs of a creature whose vitals are beyond reach.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}A blackguard can only sneak attack living creatures with discernible anatomies. Undead, constructs, oozes, plants, and incorporeal creatures lack vital areas to attack. Additionally, any creature immune to critical hits is not subject to sneak attacks.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}If a blackguard gets a sneak attack bonus from another source (such as rogue levels), the bonuses to damage stack.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Blackguards choose their spells from the following list:\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}1st level-cause fear, cure light wounds, doom, inflict light wounds, magic weapon, summon monster I*.\line 2nd level-bull\rquote s strength, cure moderate wounds, darkness, death knell, inflict moderate wounds, shatter, summon monster II*.\line 3rd level-contagion, cure serious wounds, deeper darkness, inflict serious wounds, protection from elements, summon monster III*.\line 4th level-cure critical wounds, freedom of movement, inflict critical wounds, poison, summon monster IV*.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}*Evil creatures only.\par
