{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}3-4:\tab\tab Lay on hands. Once per day, the blackguard can cure himself of \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\tab\tab damage equal to his Charisma bonus times his level. The blackguard \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\tab\tab can only cure himself or his fiendish servant with this spell-like \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\tab\tab ability.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}5-6:\tab\tab Sneak attack damage increased by +1d6.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}7-8:\tab\tab Fiendish summoning. Once per day, the blackguard can use a summon \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\tab\tab monster I spell to call forth an evil creature. For this spell, the \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\tab\tab caster level is double the blackguard\rquote s class level.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}9-10:\tab\tab Undead companion. In addition to the fiendish servant, the \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\tab\tab blackguard gains (at 5th level) a Medium-size skeleton or zombie as \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\tab\tab a companion. This companion cannot be turned or rebuked by another \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\tab\tab and gains all special bonuses as a fiendish servant when the \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\tab\tab blackguard gains levels.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}11+:\tab\tab Favored of the dark deities. Evil deities like nothing more than to \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\tab\tab see a pure heart corrupted, and thus a fallen paladin of this \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\tab\tab stature immediately gains a blackguard level for each level of \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\tab\tab paladin he trades in. For example, a character who has twelve levels \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\tab\tab of paladin can immediately become a 10th-level blackguard with all \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\tab\tab abilities if he chooses to lose ten levels of paladin. The character \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\tab\tab level of the character does not change. \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\tab\tab This, of course, is in every way a profitable trade for the evil \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\tab\tab character, since he has already lost most of the benefits he gained \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\tab\tab from having those paladin levels. However, with the loss of paladin \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\tab\tab levels, the character no longer gains extra abilities found on this \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\tab\tab table. Thus, a fallen paladin of 15th level could become a 10th-\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\tab\tab level blackguard/5th-level paladin with the first three extra \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}\tab\tab abilities on this chart because of those five levels of paladin.\par
\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlcont\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\ri4665\sb100\sa100\ul\f0 CLERIC\ulnone\par
\cf1{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Alignment: Any.  If the Cleric serves a specific deity the cleric's alignment must be within one step of his deity's, and it may not be neutral unless the deity's alignment is neutral.  Choosing to serve a specific deity is optional.\line\cf0 Hit Die: d8.\line Class Skills: The cleric's class skills (and the key ability for each skill) are Concentration (Con), Craft (Int), Diplomacy (Cha), Heal (Wis), Knowledge (arcana) (Int), Knowledge (religion) (Int), Profession (Wis), Scry (Int, exclusive skill), and Spellcraft (Int). \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Domains and Class Skills: A cleric who chooses Animal or Plant as one of his domains also has Knowledge (nature) (Int) as a class skill. A cleric who chooses Knowledge as one of his domains also has all Knowledge (Int) skills as class skills. A cleric who chooses Travel as one of his domains also has Wilderness Lore as a class skill. A cleric who chooses Trickery as one of his domains also has Bluff (Cha), Disguise (Cha), and Hide (Dex) as class skills. See Deity, Domains, and Domain Spells, below, for more information. \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Armor and Weapon Proficiency: Clerics are proficient with all simple weapons. Clerics are proficient with all types of armor (light, medium, and heavy) and with shields. Note that armor check penalties for armor heavier than leather apply to the skills Balance, Climb, Escape Artist, Hide, Jump, Move Silently, Pick Pocket, and Tumble. \par
